@Dominic

I didn't include this this tidbit in the post because I figured it wasn't relevant, but when the module wasn't initially working, I did end up bridging the 3VSB+ to the 3V assuming that I did actually need to hook up 3VSB+. It turns out that when I did that and had slotted the module correctly (the second time), the motherboard refused to power on (Pressing the power button and nothing happens). Only when I removed the bridge, I was able to get the board to boot.

As for the SLB9665TT20 modules, I bought them off AliExpress. You should be able to find them quite easily. I paid about $2 per chip.
